<p><span class=rvts1>Demo: GUI-support&nbsp; </span><span class=rvts8>(october 2008)</span></p>
<p>&nbsp; </p>
<p>This module is an integral part of PyLab_W</p>
<p>Coming from Delphi, the design of GUI in Python feels rather clumsy. Creating a GUI in wxPython isn't easy. There are several tools to make this design easier, but I couldn't get one of them working good enough. There is one that works (XRC), but I hate it, I find XRC a typical example of "Why should we do it easy, as it can be done complex". Therefor I created a simple solution, which is even more powerful than XRC. </p>
<p>Gui_support is a library, with the following features</p>
<ul style="text-indent: 0px; margin-left: 24px; list-style-position: outside;">
<li><span class=rvts10>create a GUI</span> from a string </li>
<li><span class=rvts10>implicit import</span> of (special) component types </li>
<li><span class=rvts10>Save and Restore settings</span> of all GUI-components </li>
<li><span class=rvts10>convenience procedures</span> to save typing </li>
<li><span class=rvts10>F12 preview</span> of the GUI within the PW-IDE </li>
</ul>
